   "source": [
    "## Simplified Model of &beta;-lactam Diffusion, Efflux, and Hydrolysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "70f7d8b6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Hydrolysis Process"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "426d556e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from ecoli.processes.antibiotics import antibiotic_hydrolysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "37a59247",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The antibiotic hydrolysis process describes the following reaction:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ S \\leftrightharpoons S_H $$\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's assume that this follows Michaelis-Menten Kinetics:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ v = \\frac{k_{cat}[E][S]}{K_M + [S]} $$\n",
    "\n",
    "By default, we have the following values:\n",
    "\n",
    "* $K_M = 1 \\times 10^{-3}$ mM\n",
    "* $[E] = 1 \\times 10^{-3}$ mM (this is constant)\n",
    "* $[S]_0 = 1 \\times 10^{-3}$ mM\n",
    "* $k_{cat} = 1$ $s^{-1}$\n",
    "* $[S_H]_0 = 0$ mM"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "495913ac",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "{'Km': <Quantity(0.001, 'millimole / liter')>,\n",
      " 'initial_catalyst': 0.001,\n",
      " 'initial_target_internal': 0.001,\n",
      " 'kcat': <Quantity(1, '1 / second')>}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pprint({\n",
    "    key: val\n",
    "    for key, val in antibiotic_hydrolysis.AntibioticHydrolysis.defaults.items()\n",
    "    if key in ('Km', 'initial_catalyst', 'initial_target_internal', 'kcat')\n",
    "})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cedbde1f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "If we simulate the process for 10 seconds, we get behavior that looks about right:"
   ]

   "id": "b9fb2a7a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Efflux Process"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "320aa1b3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from ecoli.processes.antibiotics import antibiotic_transport"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "425c999f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The antibiotic hydrolysis process describes the following reaction:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ S_I \\leftrightharpoons S_E $$\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's assume that this follows Michaelis-Menten kinetics:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ v = \\frac{k_{cat}[E][S_I]}{K_M + [S_I]} $$\n",
    "\n",
    "By default, we have the following values:\n",
    "\n",
    "* $K_M = 1 \\times 10^{-3}$ mM\n",
    "* $[E] = 1 \\times 10^{-3}$ mM (this is constant)\n",
    "* $[S_I]_0 = 1 \\times 10^{-3}$ mM\n",
    "* $[S_E]_0 = 0$ mM\n",
    "* $k_{cat} = 1$ $s^{-1}$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "2775d4f9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "{'Km': <Quantity(0.001, 'millimole / liter')>,\n",
      " 'initial_external_antibiotic': 0,\n",
      " 'initial_internal_antibiotic': 0.001,\n",
      " 'initial_pump': 0.001,\n",
      " 'kcat': <Quantity(1, '1 / second')>}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pprint({\n",
    "    key: val\n",
    "    for key, val in antibiotic_transport.AntibioticTransport.defaults.items()\n",
    "    if key in ('Km', 'initial_pump', 'initial_internal_antibiotic', 'kcat', 'initial_external_antibiotic')\n",
    "})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ba748b93",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "If we simulate the process for 10 seconds, we get behavior that looks about right:"
   ]
  },
  {

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

    "efflux_demo_fig"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "55d0aaad",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note that there is an extra step for exported molecules. The efflux process writes the number of molecules to export to the `exchanges` store, and then a second process, `NonSpatialEnvironment`, updates the fields and the transport process's `external` store based on those exchanges. To avoid the 1-timestep lag that this extra step would normally introduce, we make `NonSpatialEnvironment` a `Deriver`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Here we are using a cell volume of 1.2 fL and an environment volume of 1 fL."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b7e82c19",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can compare the simulated results to what we get from doing the Michaelis-Menten calculations directly:"
   ]
  },
  {

   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "cd188787",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x500 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "efflux_expected = antibiotic_transport.get_expected_demo_data()\n",
    "antibiotic_transport.get_demo_vs_expected_plot(efflux_demo_data, efflux_expected)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fa251c60",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "There is very good agreement between the simulated and expected timeseries."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "39256c19",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Diffusion Process"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "253b1708",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from ecoli.processes.antibiotics import fickian_diffusion"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f2853fd2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The diffusion process describes the following reaction:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ S_E \\leftrightharpoons S_I $$\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's assume that this follows Fickian diffusion:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ rate_{mol} = P \\cdot A \\cdot m ([S_I] - [S_E]) \\Delta t $$\n",
    "\n",
    "Notice that $rate_{mol}$ has units of moles/sec and is positive when the net flux is out of the cell.\n",
    "\n",
    "By default, we have the following values:\n",
    "\n",
    "* $P = 1 \\times 10^{-5}$ cm/sec\n",
    "* $A = 132$ $\\frac{cm^2}{mg}$\n",
    "* $[S_I]_0 = 0$ mM\n",
    "* $[S_E]_0 = 1 \\times 10^{-3}$ mM\n",
    "* $m = 300$ fg (this is constant)\n",
    "\n",
    "This equation and $A$ come from:\n",
    "\n",
    "> Nagano, K., & Nikaido, H. (2009). Kinetic Behavior of the Major Multidrug Efflux Pump AcrB of Escherichia coli. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, 106(14), 5854–5858. https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.0901695106\n",
    "\n",
    "The permeability was chosen to make the half-equilibration time 1-10 seconds based on Figure 1 in:\n",
    "\n",
    "> Nikaido, H. (1989). Outer membrane barrier as a mechanism of antimicrobial resistance. Antimicrobial Agents and Chemotherapy, 33(11), 1831–1836. https://doi.org/10.1128/AAC.33.11.1831"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "9058982b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [

      "                   'internal': {'antibiotic': 0},\n",
      "                   'mass_global': {'dry_mass': <Quantity(300, 'femtogram')>},\n",
      "                   'volume_global': {'volume': <Quantity(1.2, 'femtoliter')>}},\n",
      " 'permeability': <Quantity(1e-05, 'centimeter / second')>,\n",
      " 'surface_area_mass_ratio': <Quantity(132.0, 'centimeter ** 2 / milligram')>}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pprint({\n",
    "    key: val\n",
    "    for key, val in fickian_diffusion.FickianDiffusion.defaults.items()\n",
    "    if key in ('permeability', 'surface_area_mass_ratio', 'initial_state',)\n",
    "})"
   ]
  },

    "There is very good agreement between the simulated and expected timeseries. Also notice that the concentrations reach equilibrium at the value we would expect (about $0.5 \\times 10^{-3}$ mM because the internal and external volumes are about equal) and do so within 10 seconds, as we expected based on the half-equilibration time."
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "37003b9c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Simple Antibiotics Composite"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a7cd534b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's begin with a simple composite of the three processes above. To derive the periplasm volume from the cell volume, we'll also add a shape deriver."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "dddea2ca",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from vivarium.plots.topology import plot_topology\n",
    "from vivarium.library.units import units\n",
    "from vivarium.core.composition import composite_in_experiment, simulate_experiment\n",
    "\n",
    "from ecoli.composites.antibiotics_simple import SimpleAntibioticsCell, INITIAL_EXTERNAL_ANTIBIOTIC\n",
    "from ecoli.processes.antibiotics.nonspatial_environment import NonSpatialEnvironment\n",
    "\n",
    "def examine_simple_composite():\n",
    "    composer = SimpleAntibioticsCell()\n",
    "    composite = composer.generate()\n",
    "\n",
    "    plot_settings = {\n",
    "        'dashed_edges': True,\n",
    "        'graph_format': 'hierarchy',\n",
    "        'node_distance': 5,\n",
    "        'font_size': 10,\n",
    "        'node_labels': {\n",
    "            'fickian_diffusion': 'diffusion',\n",
    "            'shape_deriver': 'shape',\n",
    "        },\n",
    "        'coordinates': {\n",
    "            'periplasm': (1, 4),\n",
    "            'fluxes': (2, 4),\n",
    "            'boundary': (3, 4),\n",
    "\n",
    "            'periplasm\\nconcs': (0.5, 3),\n",
    "            'periplasm\\nglobal': (1.5, 3),\n",
    "\n",
    "            'boundary\\nexchanges': (2.5, 3),\n",
    "            'boundary\\nexternal': (3.5, 3),\n",
    "\n",
    "            'efflux': (0.5, 0),\n",
    "            'hydrolysis': (1.5, 0),\n",
    "            'fickian_diffusion': (2.5, 0),\n",
    "            'shape_deriver': (3.5, 0),\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "    topology_fig = plot_topology(composite, plot_settings)\n",
    "\n",
    "    initial_state = composite.initial_state()\n",
    "    return topology_fig, initial_state\n",
    "\n",
    "simple_composite_topology_fig, simple_composite_initial = examine_simple_composite()"
   ]
  },

   ]

      "              'mass': <Quantity(1339, 'femtogram')>,\n",

      "                         'antibiotic_hydrolyzed': 0,\n",
      "                         'beta-lactamase': 0.001,\n",
      "                         'pump': 0.001},\n",
      "               'global': {'mmol_to_counts': <Quantity(2.16797067e+23, 'femtoliter / mole')>,\n",

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cb957c6b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now let's run a some simulations to see the effects of each process:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "id": "1ed21b4e",
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "Simulation ID: 47c2bbce-2c83-11ec-873b-94f6d615b5b6\n",
      "Created: 10/13/2021 at 20:11:29\n",
      "Completed in 0.524067 seconds\n",
      "\n",
      "Simulation ID: 4833c3f0-2c83-11ec-873b-94f6d615b5b6\n",
      "Created: 10/13/2021 at 20:11:30\n",
      "Completed in 0.541325 seconds\n",
      "\n",
      "Simulation ID: 48a106d6-2c83-11ec-873b-94f6d615b5b6\n",
      "Created: 10/13/2021 at 20:11:31\n",
      "Completed in 0.438703 seconds\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 26,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def simulate_simple_composite(config=None):\n",
    "    config = config or {}\n",
    "    composite = SimpleAntibioticsCell(config).generate()\n",
    "    env = NonSpatialEnvironment({\n",
    "        'concentrations': {\n",
    "            'antibiotic': INITIAL_EXTERNAL_ANTIBIOTIC,\n",
    "        },\n",
    "        'internal_volume': 1.2 * units.fL,\n",
    "        'env_volume': 1 * units.mL,\n",
    "    })\n",
    "    composite.merge(\n",
    "        composite=env.generate(),\n",
    "        topology={\n",
    "            'nonspatial_environment': {\n",
    "                'external': ('external',),\n",
    "                'exchanges': ('exchanges',),\n",
    "                'fields': ('environment', 'fields'),\n",
    "                'dimensions': ('environment', 'dimensions'),\n",
    "                'global': ('global',),\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    exp = composite_in_experiment(\n",
    "        composite,\n",
    "        initial_state=composite.initial_state(),\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    data = simulate_experiment(exp, {'total_time': 10})\n",
    "    return data\n",
    "\n",
    "def simulate_simple_composite_knockouts():\n",
    "    data_wt = simulate_simple_composite()\n",
    "    data_efflux_ko = simulate_simple_composite({\n",
    "        'efflux': {\n",
    "            'initial_pump': 0,\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    })\n",
    "    data_beta_lactamase_ko = simulate_simple_composite({\n",
    "        'hydrolysis': {\n",
    "            'initial_catalyst': 0,\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    })\n",
    "    assert data_wt['time'] == data_efflux_ko['time'] == data_beta_lactamase_ko['time']\n",
    "    time = data_wt['time']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    datasets = {\n",
    "        'Wildtype': data_wt,\n",
    "        'Efflux Pump Knockout': data_efflux_ko,\n",
    "        'Beta-Lactamase Knockout': data_beta_lactamase_ko,\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(nrows=2, sharex=True)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for label, data in datasets.items():\n",
    "        ax1.plot(time, data['periplasm']['concs']['antibiotic'], label=label)\n",
    "        ax2.plot(time, data['periplasm']['concs']['antibiotic_hydrolyzed'], label=label)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    ax1.set_title('Periplasmic Antibiotic')\n",
    "    ax2.set_title('Hydrolyzed Periplasmic Antibiotic')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ax2.set_xlabel('Time (s)')\n",
    "    ax1.set_ylabel('Concentration (mM)')\n",
    "    ax2.set_ylabel('Concentration (mM)')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ax2.legend()\n",
    "        \n",
    "    fig.tight_layout()\n",
    "        \n",
    "    return fig\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \n",
    "simulate_simple_composite_knockouts()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7d7fe983",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Notice that above, while we have a `NonSpatialEnvironment`, we don't have a `LocalField` process to apply cellular exchanges to the environment. This means that the environmental antibiotic concentrations are fixed."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d1bebdd7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Colony Simulation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "993f9086",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To run a colony simulation, we add the following processes:\n",
    "\n",
    "* GrowthRate: Simple exponential growth. This is a stub for metabolism-driven growth.\n",
    "* DeriveGlobals: Derive some useful cell properties like mass and volume.\n",
    "* DivideCondition: Divide once the cell doubles in size.\n",
    "* MetaDivision: Handle division.\n",
    "* LocalField: Apply cellular exchanges to the environment.\n",
    "\n",
    "This gives us a `GrowDivideAntibioticsCell` composite that we can embed inside a `Lattice` composite to get colony simulations. Note that these simulations use unrealistic parameters (especially an accelerated growth rate). This is just to quickly show that colonies work."
   ]
  },
